
[1]infidelity

   INFIDEL'ITY, n. [L. infidelitas.]

   1. In general, want of faith or belief; a withholding of credit.

   2. Disbelief of the inspiration of the Scriptures, or the divine
   original of christianity; unbelief.

   There is no doubt that vanity is one principal cause of infidelity.

   3. Unfaithfulness, particularly in married persons; a violation of the
   marriage covenant by adultery or lewdness.

   4. Breach of trust; treachery; deceit; as the infidelity of a friend or
   a servant. In this sense, unfaithfulness is most used.
